\n\nThe stored strings use URI userinfo percent-encoding so parsed URIs can be rendered without\nlosing percent-encoding choices (for example, `%3A` versus `:`).\n\nNote: embedding passwords in URIs is deprecated per RFC 9110 Section 4.2.4. Avoid using the\npassword field in new code, and never include it in logs or error messages.\n\nReference: https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc3986.html#section-3.2.1\n","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.UserInfo","kind":"structure","line":98,"name":"Std.Http.URI.UserInfo","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.lean#L98-L119"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofPort\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">URI</span>.<span class=\"name\">Scheme</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofPort</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">port</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt16\">UInt16</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme\">Scheme</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the URI scheme for a given port: `\"https\"` for 443, `\"http\"` otherwise.\n","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofPort","kind":"def","line":90,"name":"Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofPort","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.lean#L90-L94"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.defaultPort\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">URI</span>.<span class=\"name\">Scheme</span>.<span class=\"name\">defaultPort</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">scheme</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme\">Scheme</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#UInt16\">UInt16</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the default port number for this URI scheme: 443 for `https`, 80 for everything else.\n","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.defaultPort","kind":"def","line":84,"name":"Std.Http.URI.Scheme.defaultPort","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.lean#L84-L88"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString!\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">URI</span>.<span class=\"name\">Scheme</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofString!</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme\">Scheme</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a `Scheme` from a string, normalizing to lowercase. Panics if invalid.\n","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString!","kind":"def","line":76,"name":"Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString!","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.lean#L76-L82"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">URI</span>.<span class=\"name\">Scheme</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofString?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme\">Scheme</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempts to create a `Scheme` from a string, normalizing to lowercase.\nReturns `none` if the scheme is invalid per RFC 3986 Section 3.1.\n","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString?","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"Std.Http.URI.Scheme.ofString?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.lean#L64-L74"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.instInhabitedScheme\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">URI</span>.<span class=\"name\">instInhabitedScheme</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <a href=\"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.Scheme\">Scheme</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Http/Data/URI/Basic.html#Std.Http.URI.instInhabitedScheme","kind":"instance","line":59,"name":"Std.Http.URI.instInhabitedScheme","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a